      <prefercite id="aspace_5587864cf7fd5084a85e57832fd5c598">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Waltraude Woods, Senior Architect/Planner, Yale University, Records Documenting the History of Yale Buildings and Grounds (RU 965). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <arrangement id="aspace_583eebf1b1b7bb9da25acfc2f798328c">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged by accession.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_d4dd5b1d58afd130e8c2afb69c5a7a73">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of maps, studies, news clippings, research notes, presentation panels, and assorted data compiled by Waltraude (Val) Woods, senior architect/planner at Yale Office of Facilities, documenting the history of campus planning and buildings and grounds at Yale University.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
